  "summary": "## Summary: Remove the Brain Knowledge (to be replaced by Pages.)\n\n### Changes Implemented\n- Deleted the Brain page with all three tabs (Chat, Knowledge, Graph)\n- Deleted the ThoughtGraph D3.js visualization component\n- Deleted all 12 Brain API routes (chat, sessions, thoughts, graph, reminders, clips, links)\n- Removed Brain from the desktop sidebar navigation (SideNav)\n- Removed Brain from the mobile bottom navigation tabs (MobileBottomNav)\n- Removed Ctrl+B keyboard shortcut for Brain (AppShell)\n- Removed \"Open Brain\" and \"Capture to Brain\" commands from the Command Palette\n- Cleaned up unused BrainIcon, BrainTabIcon, BrainCaptureIcon functions\n- Cleaned up unused useRouter import in AppShell\n- Preserved Microsoft Graph API routes (app/api/graph/) which are unrelated\n\n### Files Modified\n- `components/ui/SideNav.tsx` — Removed brain nav item, icon, and isActive check\n- `components/ui/MobileBottomNav.tsx` — Removed brain tab, icon, and isActive check\n- `components/ui/AppShell.tsx` — Removed Ctrl+B shortcut, removed unused useRouter\n- `components/ui/CommandPalette.tsx` — Removed brain navigation and action commands, removed BrainCaptureIcon\n\n### Files Deleted\n- `app/(app)/brain/page.tsx`\n- `components/brain/ThoughtGraph.tsx`\n- `app/api/brain/chat/route.ts`\n- `app/api/brain/sessions/route.ts`\n- `app/api/brain/sessions/[sessionId]/route.ts`\n- `app/api/brain/thoughts/route.ts`\n- `app/api/brain/thoughts/graph/route.ts`\n- `app/api/brain/thoughts/[thoughtId]/route.ts`\n- `app/api/brain/thoughts/[thoughtId]/reminders/route.ts`\n- `app/api/brain/thoughts/[thoughtId]/links/route.ts`\n- `app/api/brain/thoughts/[thoughtId]/links/[linkId]/route.ts`\n- `app/api/brain/thoughts/[thoughtId]/link-search/route.ts`\n- `app/api/brain/reminders/route.ts`\n- `app/api/brain/clips/route.ts`\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- Database tables (brainThoughts, brainChatSessions, brainChatMessages, brainThoughtLinks, brainThoughtReminders) still exist in the schema — these can be removed in a future migration if desired\n- The Brain chat endpoint referenced meetings, emails, decisions, and action items for context — the Pages feature should eventually provide similar AI context capabilities\n- Microsoft Graph API routes (app/api/graph/) were preserved as they handle email integration, not the knowledge graph"
